    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Identify existing telemetry pattern in `Sprk.Bff.Api` (likely `ILogger` + `TelemetryClient` or `ActivitySource`). Reuse the pattern for consistency.</step>
    <step order="2">Author a `RoutingDispatchTelemetry` helper that accepts a struct of tier-1 fields and emits a single App Insights custom event. Fields: `{ tenantId, sessionId, filesCount, manifestPresent, filesAllAgree, decidersInvoked, selectedPlaybookId, selectionConfidence, perFileLatencyMs[], totalLatencyMs, outcome }`.</step>
    <step order="3">Wire emission at the END of `PlaybookDispatcher.DispatchAsync` â€” always emits one event per dispatch (success + failure paths).</step>
    <step order="4">Author negative-assert unit test: build a `RoutingDispatchTelemetry` event with sentinel user message ("SECRET_USER_TEXT_DO_NOT_LOG") and file content ("SECRET_FILE_CONTENT_DO_NOT_LOG"). Run; serialize emitted event; grep result for those sentinels â€” must NOT appear.</step>
    <step order="5">Author positive unit test: assert standard tier-1 fields ARE emitted with correct values.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`. All pass.</step>
    <step order="7">Spot-check App Insights query (post-deploy) â€” verify event surfaces with expected fields; verify no leakage.</step>
    <step order="8">Measure BFF publish size; report delta.</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 117 â†’ âś…; current-task.md â†’ ready for 118.</step>
  </steps>

